{{Quote|Less than two standard hours after this morning's secession of Ando and Sy Myrth was made official, jubilant anti-Republic protestors filled the streets of Quantill City's busy Raquish Thoroughfare, celebrating the separation.|HoloNet News report|<ref name="HNN" />}}
The '''Raquish Thoroughfare''' was a busy roadway featuring several streets in [[Quantill City]],<ref name="HNN" /> the largest [[City/Legends|city]]<ref name="CSWE Quantill">{{CSWECite|III|59|Quantill City}}</ref> and [[Capital/Legends|capital]] of [[Ando/Legends|Ando]],<ref name="DC">''[[Dangerous Covenants]]''</ref> the [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim]] [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of the [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Aqualish/Legends|Aqualish]] [[Species/Legends|species]].<ref name="CSWE Ando">{{CSWECite|I|30|Ando}}</ref> It shared its name with the [[Raquish system/Legends|Raquish system]]<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> and the [[Battle of Raquish]], which was fought in [[39 BBY/Legends|39 BBY]] and pitted the [[Spiverelda/Legends|Spiverelda]], the group of [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] [[Colonist/Legends|colonized]] by the Aqualish and being under the influence of Ando, against<ref name="EGTW">''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]''</ref> the fifteen Aqualish-settled planets known as the [[Andoan Free Colonies/Legends|Andoan Free Colonies]].<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|I|30|Andosha II}}</ref>

In [[23 BBY/Legends|13:2:28]], less than two [[Standard hour/Legends|standard hours]] after Ando officially [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|seceded]] from the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], the streets of the Raquish Thoroughfare were filled with jubilant Aqualish of various backgrounds and from different areas of their homeworld who protested against the [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] government. The protesters subsequently converged in the city square of Quantill City. The event was later noted by an issue of the [[HoloNet News CoCo District Edition|CoCo District Edition]] of the [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]].<ref name="HNN" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Raquish Thoroughfare was introduced in [[HoloNet News Vol. 531 45|''HoloNet News Vol. 531 #45'']], an issue of the [[HoloNet News (original website)|representation]] of the [[in-universe]] [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]]<ref name="HNN" /> that was written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Paul Ens]]<ref name="Credits">{{HoloNetNewsWeb||credits.html|Credits}}</ref> and published by [[March 10]], [[2002]].<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=threads/5990764|board=Literature|thread=The Official HoloNetNews Discussion Thread|user=IAmTheDarkSide|date=2002-03-10|time=7:24 PM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002154704/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-official-holonetnews-discussion-thread.5990764}}</ref>

